      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS BLUE STORK (6) successfully took a step up in grade when she came from one spot wider than this and dug deep to get home by a neck at Newcastle last week. That gave her seven wins and two placings in nine outings for the stable and she has only once been beaten in five tries here. Can deliver again. LOU WILL NZ (1) made an impressive start for Seaton Grima when cruising home by 18 metres at Newcastle last week. Up in grade but can take advantage of the ace draw. FIRE FOX NZ (10) draws on the back row this time but has done well to place in his last two appearances, beaten just a head at this circuit and distance last week. Tricky draw for CAPTAIN RITCHIE (9) but he will be rock-hard fit after four starts back from a spell and has performed well at his last couple.",
